1
00:01:30,890 --> 00:01:35,000
[Dream of Golden Years]

2
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:39,460
[2020]

3
00:01:43,430 --> 00:01:45,360
Having a birthday on New Year's Day

4
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:46,400
means you clash with

5
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,259
the entire world's celebration.

6
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:49,000
It means

7
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,840
you're always forgotten
amidst the revelry.

8
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:54,840
Everyone looks forward to the new year,

9
00:01:55,350 --> 00:01:56,479
and no one cares

10
00:01:57,430 --> 00:01:59,000
that you're a year older.

11
00:02:06,420 --> 00:02:07,350
Happy Birthday,

12
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:08,600
Xia Xiaolan.

13
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:14,470
[Episode 17: Happy Birthday to You]

14
00:02:16,910 --> 00:02:17,640
Will this do?

15
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:18,680
Yes.

16
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,120
That's all.

17
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:20,710
Okay.

18
00:02:20,910 --> 00:02:21,750
Please wait a moment.

19
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:22,680
Okay, thank you.

20
00:02:23,910 --> 00:02:24,590
Earlier,

21
00:02:24,710 --> 00:02:25,520
I told your mom

22
00:02:25,630 --> 00:02:27,190
that we should come try this restaurant

23
00:02:27,190 --> 00:02:29,120
after I got back from my business trip.

24
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,579
I really didn't expect you

25
00:02:30,710 --> 00:02:32,190
to be free today.

26
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,310
Will your clothing store

27
00:02:34,310 --> 00:02:35,400
be okay

28
00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:36,690
without you there?

29
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:39,440
Looks like he doesn't want me to be here.

30
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:41,810
A boss needs to trust

31
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:42,700
her employees.

32
00:02:43,150 --> 00:02:44,140
Mr. Tang, you usually

33
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:45,470
have a lot on your plate.

34
00:02:45,710 --> 00:02:46,840
Focusing on the big picture
and not sweating the small stuff—

35
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,430
you know that better than I do.

36
00:02:48,430 --> 00:02:49,430
Nice restaurant.

37
00:02:49,430 --> 00:02:50,000
Yes.

38
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:53,590
Let's get a table first.

39
00:02:54,030 --> 00:02:54,960
Tang?

40
00:02:56,430 --> 00:02:57,560
What a coincidence.

41
00:02:58,590 --> 00:02:59,150
Hello.

42
00:03:01,670 --> 00:03:03,710
This must be Liu Fen, right?

43
00:03:05,030 --> 00:03:05,520
Hello.

44
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:07,280
Hello, I am.

45
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,020
When eating Western food,

46
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:12,260
do you know which hand holds the knife

47
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:13,720
and which holds the fork?

48
00:03:14,710 --> 00:03:15,310
I forgot.

49
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:16,930
Don't treat it
like when you were in the countryside,

50
00:03:16,930 --> 00:03:18,420
chopping pig feed with a blade.

51
00:03:18,420 --> 00:03:19,620
If you use them wrong,

52
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:21,560
you'll embarrass yourself
in front of the foreign guests.

53
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,630
It's been so long
since the Reform and Opening-Up,

54
00:03:23,630 --> 00:03:24,960
yet some people

55
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:27,360
still like to pretend to be foreigners

56
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:28,960
and worship foreign things.

57
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:31,720
Does it matter if we use a knife and fork?

58
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:33,000
This is Shengcheng.

59
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,630
I'm paying to eat.

60
00:03:35,140 --> 00:03:36,240
If I use a knife and fork,

61
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:38,430
it's to respect their culinary culture.

62
00:03:38,430 --> 00:03:39,590
If I don't want to,

63
00:03:39,780 --> 00:03:40,740
shouldn't they

64
00:03:40,910 --> 00:03:41,630
just give me

65
00:03:41,630 --> 00:03:42,840
a pair of chopsticks?

66
00:03:43,430 --> 00:03:44,560
Right, Mr. Tang?

67
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:45,890
Xiaolan,

68
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,000
I think what you said is really good.

69
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,150
Actually,

70
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,250
where you eat

71
00:03:50,590 --> 00:03:51,630
and what utensils you use

72
00:03:51,630 --> 00:03:53,030
are not important at all.

73
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:54,820
What matters is

74
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,010
who you are eating with.

75
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:28,560
Mr. Tang,

76
00:04:29,260 --> 00:04:31,180
we don't know

77
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,510
that lady just now.

78
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,950
But she knew my mom's name.

79
00:04:35,830 --> 00:04:37,600
Shouldn't you explain?

80
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:45,720
She is my ex-wife.

81
00:04:47,070 --> 00:04:48,000
Her name is Ji Ya.

82
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,640
She studied fashion design.

83
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:51,460
She just came back from the US.

84
00:04:52,630 --> 00:04:53,720
This is probably the second time

85
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,720
I've seen her here.

86
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,390
The first time

87
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:59,750
was two weeks ago.

88
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:02,240
She came to my office looking for me.

89
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:03,600
At that time,

90
00:05:04,650 --> 00:05:05,480
she talked a lot about

91
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:06,360
the past.

92
00:05:07,190 --> 00:05:08,790
I understood what she meant,

93
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:09,920
but I

94
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,520
made it very clear to her then

95
00:05:11,870 --> 00:05:12,730
that right now,

96
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,580
there is someone I want to be with,

97
00:05:16,310 --> 00:05:17,110
someone I want

98
00:05:17,830 --> 00:05:19,630
to spend the rest of my life with.

99
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:26,560
Mom.

100
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:28,870
That...

101
00:05:30,310 --> 00:05:31,430
Ms. Ji just now—

102
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:33,670
judging by her reaction,

103
00:05:34,430 --> 00:05:36,240
what Mr. Tang said must be true.

104
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:46,610
Here, Xiaolan.

105
00:05:53,530 --> 00:05:54,000
Thank you.

106
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:54,930
You're welcome.

107
00:05:58,920 --> 00:05:59,520
Thank you.

108
00:06:02,430 --> 00:06:03,090
Mayor Tang,

109
00:06:03,310 --> 00:06:04,240
here are the chopsticks you asked for.

110
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:05,640
-Okay.
-Enjoy your meal.

111
00:06:09,390 --> 00:06:10,870
If you don't like
using the knife and fork,

112
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:12,530
I'll use chopsticks with you.

113
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:14,320
It's fine.

114
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:15,800
No need.

115
00:06:37,630 --> 00:06:38,950
Why are you two staring at me?

116
00:06:38,950 --> 00:06:40,210
Why aren't you eating?

117
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:41,510
Mom,

118
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:43,750
I only taught you once.

119
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:46,860
I didn't expect you to be so good at it.

120
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,290
I just felt I might need it someday.

121
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:51,290
I didn't expect to actually use it.

122
00:06:52,430 --> 00:06:53,690
I practiced secretly.

123
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:56,409
I didn't embarrass you, did I?

124
00:06:57,690 --> 00:06:58,280
Your mom

125
00:06:58,310 --> 00:06:59,720
uses them better than I do.

126
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:01,680
I've forgotten it should be

127
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:02,450
knife in the left hand
and fork in the right

128
00:07:02,450 --> 00:07:03,780
or the other way around.

129
00:07:06,390 --> 00:07:06,870
So,

130
00:07:07,310 --> 00:07:08,710
that's your ex-husband?

131
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:11,680
Seems like he's in a new relationship.

132
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:13,560
But this is good news.

133
00:07:13,950 --> 00:07:16,010
Looks like I've got a good chance now.

134
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:18,390
George,

135
00:07:18,870 --> 00:07:21,270
we are just business partners and friends.

136
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:25,360
I don't really want any other factors

137
00:07:25,430 --> 00:07:27,160
affecting our cooperation.

138
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:29,680
It's okay.

139
00:07:30,270 --> 00:07:31,330
It's not a big deal.

140
00:07:32,310 --> 00:07:33,190
Have a piece of this.

141
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:33,790
Thank you.

142
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,190
Xiaolan, have a piece of this.

143
00:07:35,190 --> 00:07:36,320
Thank you, Mr. Tang.

144
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:39,630
Okay.

145
00:07:40,070 --> 00:07:40,930
I'm not hungry.

146
00:07:41,270 --> 00:07:41,950
I will go.

147
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:48,760
Let's just eat.

148
00:07:49,430 --> 00:07:50,760
Try this mushroom soup.

149
00:07:53,270 --> 00:07:53,830
Goodbye.

150
00:07:54,310 --> 00:07:54,840
Bye-bye.

151
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:56,320
Excuse me.

152
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,820
I'm gonna get the bill.

153
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,310
This is such a waste.

154
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:06,120
How about I bring them over?

155
00:08:08,310 --> 00:08:08,830
Here.

156
00:08:14,270 --> 00:08:15,330
Alright, this way.

157
00:08:15,630 --> 00:08:16,230
Thank you.

158
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,360
You're welcome, Mr. Tang.

159
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:17,870
Bye.

160
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:19,120
Please come again.

161
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:20,050
Okay, thank you.

162
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:23,950
It's still early.

163
00:08:24,070 --> 00:08:25,190
And we're quite full.

164
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:26,430
How about we take a walk

165
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:27,070
to digest?

166
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,000
Sure.

167
00:08:28,270 --> 00:08:28,800
Xiaolan,

168
00:08:28,950 --> 00:08:30,280
if you have things to do,

169
00:08:30,390 --> 00:08:31,320
you can go ahead.

170
00:08:31,870 --> 00:08:32,750
Considering how well

171
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:34,350
you dealt with Jiya just now,

172
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:35,960
I'll let you off the hook.

173
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:36,390
Right.

174
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:37,600
I happen to be meeting Zhenzhu

175
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,840
to discuss something.

176
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,020
Don't stay out too late.

177
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:40,820
Go home early.

178
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:41,600
Okay.

179
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:42,789
Bye-bye.

180
00:08:47,630 --> 00:08:48,240
Let's go.

181
00:08:50,910 --> 00:08:52,200
My behavior today

182
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,780
was actually very abrupt.

183
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,780
I want to apologize to you.

184
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:56,390
I'm sorry.

185
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,280
I hope you don't mind.

186
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:00,790
There's nothing to mind.

187
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,330
It's just that after seeing your ex-wife,

188
00:09:04,510 --> 00:09:05,910
I feel even more strongly

189
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:08,920
that we aren't suitable for each other.

190
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,000
I don't know

191
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,440
what you see in me.

192
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,510
The gap between us is so big.

193
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:17,050
We can't build a life together.

194
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:19,670
If...

195
00:09:20,270 --> 00:09:21,720
I appear by your side,

196
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,760
people will laugh at you.

197
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,040
I don't think there is

198
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,260
any gap between us.

199
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,120
And you said people would laugh at me.

200
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:32,920
That's a problem for me to solve.

201
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:34,960
You must not put pressure on yourself

202
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:35,890
because of this.

203
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:38,650
Comrade Liu Fen,

204
00:09:39,270 --> 00:09:40,200
I don't mean to

205
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,050
cling to you in a malicious way.

206
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:43,080
I just feel that

207
00:09:43,790 --> 00:09:44,990
you don't dislike me.

208
00:09:46,670 --> 00:09:48,150
If I may be so bold,

209
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:51,000
perhaps you have at least

210
00:09:51,870 --> 00:09:53,670
a little bit of affection for me.

211
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:56,910
So let's just let nature take its course

212
00:09:56,910 --> 00:09:57,970
and date normally.

213
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,090
Is that okay?

214
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:24,320
I can't answer you right now.

215
00:10:26,150 --> 00:10:27,270
Can you wait for me?

216
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,000
Whatever you want to do,

217
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,150
or however you want to do it,

218
00:10:33,150 --> 00:10:34,610
I support you 100 percent.

219
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:37,900
Actually, you see.

220
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:38,870
The two of us

221
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:40,790
are already standing together now.

222
00:10:40,790 --> 00:10:42,720
And we are face-to-face like this.

223
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:44,620
There's no need for me to wait.

224
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,240
I'll give you time

225
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:47,580
to think this through.

226
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:49,440
Let's just date normally.

227
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:56,750
Watch out.

228
00:10:58,490 --> 00:10:59,350
Let me help you.

229
00:10:59,550 --> 00:11:00,440
-Okay.
-The stairs are right ahead.

230
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,600
Thank you. Thank you.

231
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:02,550
It's okay.

232
00:11:02,570 --> 00:11:03,500
You're welcome.

233
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:04,980
Be careful.

234
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:05,390
Okay.

235
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:10,750
Xia!

236
00:11:12,390 --> 00:11:13,150
Xia!

237
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:14,840
Xia!

238
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:15,440
Coming.

239
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:17,120
What's the matter? Why the rush?

240
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:17,980
Let me tell you.

241
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:18,910
I got it.

242
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:20,790
It's also a women's clothing store

243
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:22,150
across the street.

244
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:23,440
The owner is a designer

245
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:24,320
back from the US.

246
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:25,390
From the US?

247
00:11:25,790 --> 00:11:26,550
A foreigner?

248
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:27,390
No.

249
00:11:27,630 --> 00:11:29,200
She lived in the US for years.

250
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:31,130
She just came back. She's Chinese.

251
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:32,320
Her name...

252
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:34,660
She's surnamed Ji.

253
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:37,320
Ji?

254
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:38,870
Back from the US?

255
00:11:39,630 --> 00:11:40,560
Her name is Ji Ya.

256
00:11:40,580 --> 00:11:42,180
She studied fashion design.

257
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:44,020
She just came back from the US.

258
00:11:44,670 --> 00:11:46,150
It can't be that coincidental, can it?

259
00:11:46,150 --> 00:11:47,410
Alright, case solved.

260
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:48,270
Mom,

261
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:49,390
you've run into

262
00:11:49,390 --> 00:11:50,790
a jealous psycho.

263
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:52,730
What do you mean?

264
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,790
Mom and I met Mr. Tang's ex-wife

265
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:56,480
at a restaurant before.

266
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:57,390
She is that designer

267
00:11:57,390 --> 00:11:58,480
back from the US.

268
00:11:58,500 --> 00:11:59,430
Her name is Ji Ya.

269
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:01,870
I reckon

270
00:12:02,390 --> 00:12:04,050
she wants to remarry Mr. Tang.

271
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:04,720
But since

272
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:05,870
Mr. Tang is pursuing you,

273
00:12:05,870 --> 00:12:06,800
he rejected her.

274
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,600
She's now angry out of humiliation

275
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,440
and wants to compete with you

276
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:10,360
in business.

277
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:12,720
She's just a

278
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:15,120
brainless fake foreigner.

279
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:16,630
But

280
00:12:17,230 --> 00:12:18,960
she stayed in the US for a while.

281
00:12:19,270 --> 00:12:20,800
She must be sophisticated.

282
00:12:23,510 --> 00:12:24,370
Are you scared?

283
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:25,960
I...

284
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:31,610
I'm not scared.

285
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,000
That's the spirit.

286
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:35,670
Chen.

287
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:36,870
What about you?

288
00:12:36,870 --> 00:12:38,070
Why would I be scared?

289
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,130
Alright.

290
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:40,120
Then Chen,

291
00:12:40,370 --> 00:12:41,880
use all your connections.

292
00:12:41,910 --> 00:12:43,290
I want all information on Ji Ya

293
00:12:43,290 --> 00:12:44,620
and her previous works.

294
00:12:44,670 --> 00:12:46,030
After all, know the enemy and yourself,

295
00:12:46,030 --> 00:12:47,390
and you'll never be defeated.

296
00:12:47,390 --> 00:12:47,960
Okay!

297
